text.section:
While developing a safe patient lifting policy, the workgroup shall consider, based on the patient population of that nursing home, the appropriateness and effectiveness of:
Developing or enhancing patient handling hazard assessment processes;
Enhanced use of mechanical lifting devices;
Developing specialized lift teams;
Training programs for safe patient lifting required for all patient care personnel at the nursing home;
Incorporating physical space and construction design for mechanical lifting devices in any architectural plans for nursing home construction and renovation; and
Developing an evaluation process to determine the effectiveness of the policy.
